# Error model (src/errors.ts)

Four internal tagged errors — SoulNotFoundError, NoSoulsFoundError, ManifestParseError,
FileSystemError — are used by soul-fs.ts and the internal loader methods. They are never
consumed directly by external callers.

SoulLoadError is the ONLY error type that escapes the public loader API. All internal
errors are caught, logged, and re-mapped into it, so a consumer handles a single tagged
type via Effect.catchTag("SoulLoadError", ...). Keeping the loader's failure surface to
one type at the seam is the deliberate design choice this file encodes.

